Mitch McGary is a former NBA player who played college basketball for the University of Michigan from 2012 to 2014. In 2014, McGary was involved in a bar fight in Ann Arbor, Michigan, that resulted in his arrest.
According to reports, McGary got into a physical altercation with another patron at a bar called the Brown Jug. He was then escorted out of the bar by bouncers, but allegedly tried to re-enter the establishment and was denied entry. McGary then reportedly punched a bouncer in the face, which led to his arrest.
McGary was charged with one count of operating a motor vehicle while intoxicated, one count of possession of marijuana, and one count of resisting and obstructing a police officer, in addition to the assault charge related to the bar fight. He eventually pleaded guilty to the charge of operating a vehicle while intoxicated and was sentenced to a year of probation and community service.
